Teach gather_metadata to skip tool-action deps on rules_rpm's rules.

Without this, the supply_chain_tools aspect walks rpm_package's
`_extract_tool` attr (and rpmdb_merge's `_tool` attr), follows the
exec-config go_binary down into its rules_rpm-internal Go module
deps (modernc.org/sqlite, sassoftware/go-rpmutils, klauspost/compress,
golang.org/x/crypto, ...), and emits them as image SBOM components.
Those binaries don't ship in any image — they're build-time tooling
— so they shouldn't be in the SBOM.

The mechanism is the same pattern the upstream filter uses for
`go_binary: ["_*"]` etc.: rules_rpm's two custom rule kinds get
their `_`-prefixed attrs filtered.

Track in the FIXME alongside the supply-chain archive_override —
drop once an upstream PR is filed for the `user_filtered_rule_kinds.bzl`
extension point that this file's docstring promises.

diff --git a/gather_metadata/rule_filters.bzl b/gather_metadata/rule_filters.bzl
--- a/gather_metadata/rule_filters.bzl
+++ b/gather_metadata/rule_filters.bzl
@@ -29,6 +29,8 @@
     "java_wrap_cc": ["_cc_toolchain", "swig_top"],
     "py_binary": ["_*"],
     "py_extension": ["_cc_toolchain"],
+    "rpm_package": ["_*"],
+    "rpmdb_merge": ["_*"],
     "sh_binary": ["_bash_binary"],
     "_constant_gen": ["_generator"],
 }
